[DONE] ES file seeking (avio_seek for byte-based access)
[DONE] Frame rate detection from .info files
[DONE] Audio support for ES files in preview and cutting
[DONE] Preview generation for H.264/H.265

[ ] Container smartCut stutter at middle cut points (~0.14s)
    - Caused by B-frame reordering discontinuities at encode→copy transitions
    - See H264_SMART_CUT_TRACKING.md for tested approaches
    - Low priority: ES workflow works perfectly

[ ] Hardware-accelerated encoding (VAAPI/NVENC)
    - Would speed up ES cutting significantly
    - Currently uses libx264 software encoding

[ ] Auto-detect .info file or extract frame rate from stream
    - Currently requires companion .info file from demux script
    - Could parse SPS for frame rate hints

=== Priority Features (User Requests) ===

[ ] Stream change detection on file load
    - Detect resolution changes during playback
    - Detect AC3 audio format changes (e.g., stereo→5.1 or codec switch)
    - Automatically save detected change points as markers
    - Useful for finding ad breaks in DVB recordings

[ ] Video zoom to remove black bars
    - Zoom video display so top black bar is not visible
    - Useful for 16:9 content with letterboxing
    - Should be toggleable

[ ] I-Frame thumbnail browser popup
    - New popup window showing I-frames as thumbnails from current position
    - Grid layout: 6x6 thumbnails per page
    - Paginated navigation (next/prev page)
    - Double-click on thumbnail: jump to that frame position and close popup
    - Useful for quick visual navigation to scene changes

[ ] Play button in "Current Frame" window
    - Add Play/Stop button to play video from current position
    - Playback within the current frame widget (not external player)
    - Click Play again or Stop button to pause
    - Frame-by-frame control remains available

[DONE] Jump to next/prev cut in Preview dialog
    - Added "< Prev" and "Next >" buttons in preview window
    - Quickly navigate between cut points during preview review

